gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 107, Thunder 101
gameRecap.excerpt: Minnesota defeated Oklahoma City, 107-101. Anthony Edwards led Minnesota with 27 points, four rebounds, and four assists as Karl-Anthony Towns (21 points, 10 rebounds, six assists) and Rudy Gobert (12 points, 17 rebounds) totaled 33 points. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led Oklahoma City with 37 points, seven rebounds, and eight assists as Jalen Williams added 20 points. The Timberwolves are now 33-14 on the year (16-10 on the road) as the Thunder move to 32-15.
